{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Crème Pâtissière","content":["Place milk, sugar, cornflour, eggs and vanilla bean paste in mixing bowl then cook <nobr>7 min\/90°C\/speed 4<\/nobr>. Blend <nobr>5 sec\/speed 9<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl, cover surface with cling film and set aside until cool enough to refrigerate. Meanwhile, clean mixing bowl and make choux pastry."]},{"title":"Choux Pastry","content":["Preheat oven to 180°C and line 2 baking trays with baking paper.","Place water, butter, sugar and salt in mixing bowl then heat <nobr>4 min\/100°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add flour and mix <nobr>1 min 30 sec\/speed 3<\/nobr>. Remove mixing bowl and leave to stand for 10 minutes to cool.","Place mixing bowl back in position and, without measuring cup, mix at <nobr>speed 4<\/nobr> while slowly adding eggs one at a time through hole in mixing bowl lid until fully incorporated. Transfer to a pastry bag fitted with a plain 1.5 cm nozzle, or to a disposable piping bag with 1.5 cm cut off the end.","Pipe 18 logs, 10 cm long, on prepared baking trays, leaving 3-4 cm between each. Bake for 20-25 minutes (180°C) until cooked and golden - it is important not to open the oven during baking to prevent pastries from collapsing. Meanwhile, clean mixing bowl.","Make a small hole in ends of pastries, then return to the oven and bake for a further 5 minutes (180°C) until pastry is completely crisp. Transfer to a wire rack and allow to cool."]},{"title":"Assembly and Icing","content":["Once cooled, place reserved crème patissière in mixing bowl and blend <nobr>15 sec\/speed 3<\/nobr>. Transfer to a piping bag fitted with a small nozzle then pipe into prepared holes in pastries. Set aside and prepare icing.","Place a wide bowl on mixing bowl lid and weigh in icing sugar. Remove bowl then add pink food colouring paste as desired and enough water to form a very stiff icing. Dip tops of filled pastries into icing then transfer to a wire rack. Decorate with freeze-dried raspberries and leave to set.","Best served immediately."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Crème Pâtissière","content":["500 g whole milk","70 g caster sugar","40 g cornflour","2 egg yolks, from large eggs","1 tsp vanilla bean paste"]},{"title":"Choux Pastry","content":["150 g water","80 g unsalted butter, diced","15 g caster sugar","1 pinch fine sea salt","120 g plain flour","3 medium eggs"]},{"title":"Icing","content":["250 g icing sugar","2 - 3 Tbsp water, hot","pink food colouring paste, as desired","2 Tbsp freeze-dried raspberries, for decoration"]}],"id":"r130976","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-FXMuUEXE0h4\/XZWr7lLe7oI\/AAAAAAAAfvU\/ORwv4fScI50jZ5HchaQZf9t3-ANFE2zAgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_zaZ2jQLK7XKpSaNy.png","title":"Raspberry and Vanilla Éclairs","publishedAt":"2017-11-24T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"3.2 g","fat":"6.7 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"29.1 g","calories":"793 kJ \/ 190 kcal"},"usefulItems":"2 baking trays and baking paper, piping bags and nozzles, wire rack, refrigerator, oven","hintsAndTricks":["Use the seeds from 1 vanilla pod instead of the vanilla bean paste if preferred."],"basicInfo":["medium","30m","2h","18 pieces"]}